From: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
Subject: [PATCH] Fix Stage0 package registration for source packages

When using a newer bootstrap GHC (e.g., 9.6.7 to build 9.2.8), the
bootstrap has different package versions than the source. Dependencies
from bootstrap packages may request bootstrap versions (e.g.,
ghc-boot-th-9.6.7), but if the package exists in source (ghc-boot-th-9.2.8),
we must NOT call copyConf.

The problem: copyConf unregisters by package NAME (not version), so calling
it for ghc-boot-th-9.6.7 would unregister ghc-boot-th-9.2.8, causing:
  "Encountered missing or private dependencies: ghc-boot-th ==9.2.8"

This patch changes the logic:
- If package NOT in source: use copyConf (copy from bootstrap) ✓
- If package IN source: ALWAYS use buildConf, even if different version requested
- If wrong version requested for source package: error explicitly

This prevents the race condition where copyConf unregisters the source
version before another parallel task tries to use it.

--- a/hadrian/src/Rules/Register.hs
+++ b/hadrian/src/Rules/Register.hs
@@ -107,7 +107,22 @@ registerPackageRules rs stage = do

         when (pkg == compiler) $ need =<< ghcLibDeps stage

-        isBoot <- (pkg `notElem`) <$> stagePackages Stage0
+        -- Determine if this is a boot package (not in source).
+        -- CRITICAL: For packages that exist in source, we must NEVER call
+        -- copyConf, even if a different version is requested. This is because
+        -- copyConf unregisters by package NAME (not version), which would
+        -- remove the source version and cause dependency resolution failures.
+        notInSource <- (pkg `notElem`) <$> stagePackages Stage0
+        srcPkgId <- pkgIdentifier pkg
+        let confPkgId = takeBaseName conf
+            versionMismatch = confPkgId /= srcPkgId
+            -- Only use copyConf for packages truly not in source
+            isBoot = notInSource
+
+        -- If source package but wrong version requested, error explicitly
+        when (not notInSource && versionMismatch) $
+            error $ "Version mismatch: requested " ++ confPkgId ++ " but source has " ++ srcPkgId

         let ctx = Context stage pkg vanilla
         case stage of
